{
  "texts": [
    "It is worth noting that people who feel isolated or have experienced social rejection or social frustration may be a significant source of political and social disruption in today's world.",
    "If a universally available companion bot could boost their sense of social well-being and allow them to improve their social interaction skills through practice, that tool could make a sizable contribution to society.",
    "If AI is regulated such that it encourages people to treat it in a positive, pro-social way, and if carry-over effects are real, then AI becomes a potential source of enormous social and psychological good in the world.",
    "If we are to effectively tackle the ever-growing issue of what to do in response to the surge of AI in our world, we cannot continue to point out only the ways in which it is harmful.",
    "AI is here to stay, and therefore we should be pragmatic with our approach."
  ]
}